<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id74c2b001-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s300111"><num value="300111">§ 300111.</num><heading> Authority of the Comptroller General of the United States</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Comptroller General of the United States is authorized to review the corporation’s involvement in any Federal program or activity the Government carries out under law.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id74c2b002-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/110/26/s11/a">Pub. L. 110–26, § 11(a)</ref>, <date date="2007-05-11">May 11, 2007</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/121/109">121 Stat. 109</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
